OL,3,CWorshippers locked in mosque as people
OL,4,Cattacked in Glasgow unrest
OL,6,FWorshippers at Glasgow's largest
OL,7,Fmosque were locked in for their own
OL,8,Fsafety, as tensions flared following a
OL,9,Fstabbing in Northern Ireland, with
OL,10,Fpolice saying people were "attacked
OL,11,Fbecause of the colour of their skin".
OL,13,FThree men, one aged 31 and the others
OL,14,Faged 18, were arrested on Wednesday in
OL,15,FScotland's largest city following the
OL,16,Funrest, in which three members of the
OL,17,Fpublic and two police officers were
OL,18,Fhurt, Police Scotland said.
OL,20,FThe situation followed a stabbing on
OL,21,FMonday night in North Belfast.
OL,26,@rD@[OUsD@dO]
