CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781172387
OL,3,CWorshippers locked in mosque as people
OL,4,Cattacked in Glasgow unrest
OL,6,FSarwar, who is also a Glasgow MSP,
OL,7,Fadded that many of those marching in
OL,8,Fthe city were clad in balaclavas and
OL,9,Fblack hoodies, saying their behaviour
OL,10,Fwas "intimidating" to passers-by,
OL,11,F"particularly those from certain
OL,12,Fminority backgrounds".
OL,14,F"The people inside that mosque who had
OL,15,Fto be locked in with the doors locked
OL,16,Fand the gates locked surrounded by
OL,17,Fpolice, what did they have to do with
OL,18,Fthe attacker in Belfast?" he added.
OL,26,@rD@EOUrD@RO]vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781172387
OL,3,CWorshippers locked in mosque as people
OL,4,Cattacked in Glasgow unrest
OL,6,F"They would be equally horrified by
OL,7,Fthe knife attack there, they too will
OL,8,Fwant justice to prevail."
OL,10,FFirst Minister John Swinney said the
OL,11,Fscenes were unacceptable, saying,
OL,12,F"Scotland is a welcoming nation and
OL,13,Fthose who choose to make their lives
OL,14,Fhere are valued members of our
OL,15,Fcommunities."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@YO]tD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781172387
OL,3,CWorshippers locked in mosque as people
OL,4,Cattacked in Glasgow unrest
OL,6,F"I utterly condemn this behaviour and
OL,7,Fstand firmly against acts that stoke
OL,8,Fany form of violence and intolerance.
OL,9,FAnd I want to be clear ` racism,
OL,10,Fhatred and intimidation have no place
OL,11,Fin Scotland, and we must be united in
OL,12,Fstanding against it."
OL,14,FPolice Scotland said it has an
OL,15,Fappropriate policing plan in place to
OL,16,Fdeal with any escalation in disorder.
OL,18,FIts officers will also support the
OL,19,FPolice Service of Northern Ireland,
OL,20,Fensuring there is no impact to
OL,21,Fpolicing in Scotland.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
